Detailed Description

For internal use only.

Frame-specific data. The frame-specific data is used as a per-config distributed object and contains mutable, rendering-relevant data. Each rendering thread (pipe) keeps its own instance synchronized with the frame currently being rendered. The data is managed by the Config, which modifies it directly.
